slather
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:vigorous 'unscientific' fighting; unrestrained toe-to-toe boxing action
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: from the idea of slathering or plastering blows on one's opponent (often in the collocation 'slather and whack'); see OED slather sense 3 to thrash, defeat thoroughly; see also open slather; compare slather-up n.
Citations
